<br>
Rescues are similar to assassinates, except that the guy you're rescuing spawns right away, so with a ranger and a map, you can usually tell where to head to.<br>
<br>
However, an advantage with assassinates over rescues is that once the mob spawns, you can also lull your way through if you have an enchanter/bard/cleric, particularly if you're running low on time.<br>
