<br>
I love pulling on high risk Adventures myself. While it is pretty damn hard, i gotta admit i learned alot about pulling that i didnt really understand before LDoN came out from watching .....fawy heh. <br>
<br>
I used to try to pull everything to the room we were at...which caused the mob to run along the straightest  path to the door(maybe this is common knowledge and im just lame /shrug but it seemed pretty cool to me) which pulled the mob in the middle of the room quite often. <br>
<br>
Walking into the room..and pulling the mob away from the center and having everyone just move to the near corner of the mob often prevents adds. I wish i knew how to make pics /shrug oh well. <br>
<br>
There are a few other things i learned about pulling really but i cant think of specifics atm cuz ive hardly played for the last month cuz my comp died =/.<br>
<br>
Dont be afraid (if you aint the tank) to run around like a scared little girl, if ya got aggro and might die..yes you can out run the mobs so ya wont take damage by kiting, it gives your chanter/bard/healer time to do what they need to do to keep your over aggro'n ass alive. <br>
<br>
I know alot of people think i live through High risk cuz i just got alot of hps..while thats partially true...i admit that i do run like a nome from a troll when i know im gonna get my ass kicked.<br>
<br>
Chanters...get color cloud..its HUGE in LDoN<br>
<br>
Clerics: ALWAYS make sure your int casters have Bulwark of vie on.  If you think you are annoying by asking them if they have it on...too damn bad..its better to be annoying than to have a dead chanter(which often means dead group) cuz he/she didnt have it on. I know many already do this but if ya got a pally in the group..make sure you CALL when you do div arb, and hope that pally has a brain and casts group heals. Thats gotta be the most efficient way of healing ive ever seen (besides CH of course)<br>
<br>
Mages: hi<br>
Wizards: i dont know shit about wizards so i cant give any advice...fuck it i dont know much about ANY class cept chanter /shrug hah<br>
